rk-based learning, better use of labor market information, accountability=
 for employment outcomes). Since then, agencies have awarded over 15 comp=
etitive job-training grants that total more than $1.5 billion, with an ad=
ditional 12 competitive grants of more than $800 million to be awarded ov=
er the remainder of 2016 that incorporate the job-driven training element=
s. More details on progress can be found here [ https://www.whitehouse.go=
v/sites/default/files/docs/job-driven_training_and_apprenticeship_progres=
s_report.pdf ].=20
